Sure! Use a Builder trait that lets you set fields in order. Example:

```rust
trait ConfigBuilder {
    fn build(&self) -> Config;
}

impl ConfigBuilder for Config {
    fn build(self) -> Self { self }
}

fn main() {
  let cfg = Config::new().set_x(5).build();
}
```
You can call `Config::new().set_x(5).build()` and the builder owns its state, so no dangling references.

Think of a newtype as a new type whose only value is an inner one—RAII means the value is dropped when you go out of scope. Example:

```rust
struct Byte = u8;

impl Drop for Byte {
    fn drop(&mut self) { panic!("dispose"); }
}
```
When the `Byte` goes out of scope, its destructor runs, protecting your pipeline.

